The paper discusses the impact of spatial multiplexing on the throughput of an ultra-dense mmWave AP network, which involves network topology modeling and analysis of latency, coverage probability, and network throughput. This topic is closely related to the fields of network infrastructure (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), signal processing (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
